So, \( \gcd(24, 1199) = 1 \).

Now, we need to find \( x_0 \) and \( k_0 \) such that:
\[ 24x_0 - 1199k_0 = 1 \]

We can use the sequence of quotients and remainders to express \( 1 \) in terms of \( 24 \) and \( 1199 \):
\[ 1 = 11 - 2 \times 5 = 11 - 2 \times (11 - 2 \times 2) = 11 - 2 \times 11 + 4 \times 2 = 4 \times 2 - 2 \times 11 \]
